						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I. Year 22: A.D. 929.</hi></p>						

						<p>Mutilaled and the right side of the inscription is completely lost. Seems to record a gift of 90 sheep by Māḍilaṉ Duvēdi-cheṭṭi •••Sōmāsi, for lighting a lamp in the temple of Samaparēśvarattu Mahādēva at [Nalur], a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> in [Chē]ṟṟūr-kūṟṟam. The 90 sheep were distributed to three families of shepherds.</p>						

						</summary>
